car_crashes¶

Accidents in the states of the USA are examined. This is the data set of the cause of the accidents and the cost to the accident insurance companies.

total -> Number of drivers involved in fatal collisions per billion miles (5.90023.900)

speeding -> Percentage Of Drivers Involved In Fatal Collisions Who Were Speeding (1.7929.450)

alcohol -> Percentage Of Drivers Involved In Fatal Collisions Who Were Alcohol-Impaired (1.59310.038)

not_distracted -> Percentage Of Drivers Involved In Fatal Collisions Who Were Not Distracted (1.76023.661)

no_previous -> Percentage Of Drivers Involved In Fatal Collisions Who Had Not Been Involved In Any Previous Accidents (5.90021.280)

ins_premium -> Car Insurance Premiums (641.9601301.520)

ins_losses -> Losses incurred (get or receive) by insurance companies for collisions per insured driver (82.75194.780)

abbrev -> USA states

plt.ylabel("insurance loss")
plt.show()

Inference: There appears to be a positive correlation between the total number of car crashes and the insurance losses incurred. This suggests that as the total number of car crashes increases, the insurance losses also tend to increase.
